**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion (hs : #s < c) : #(⋃ a ∈ s, t a ‹_›) < c ↔ ∀ a (ha : a ∈ s), # (t a ha) < c := by ```
This should be a `lemma` rather than an `instance` because it has non-typeclass arguments.
I now realise this can indeed be an instance because the non-typeclass arguments appear in the type of the desired instance. You should change it back: sorry for the bad advice before.

```

    · exact Exists.imp (by tauto) ih
```

```suggestion

```

We used the primed tactic alternatives heavily during porting but these days we prefer unprimed versions:
```suggestion
  refine ⟨fun S hSc hS => ?_⟩
```
(please make similar changes to the other uses of `refine'` where applicable below)

```suggestion
theorem IsRegular.nat_lt {c : Cardinal} (H : c.IsRegular) (n : ℕ) : n < c :=
```

```suggestion
theorem card_lt_of_card_iUnion_lt {ι α : Type u} {t : ι → Set α} {c : Cardinal}
    (h : #(⋃ i, t i) < c) (i : ι) : #(t i) < c :=
 lt_of_le_of_lt (Cardinal.mk_le_mk_of_subset <| subset_iUnion _ _) h
```
As above, this is an example of our [Hypotheses Left of Colon](https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/style.html#hypotheses-left-of-colon) style.
I see that my suggested rename got dropped. Was this intentional? (It is possible there is a naming convention in this corner of the library with which I am not familiar.)
I’m not sure how I missed that, sorry. I’ll change that!
It's easier for me to leave this unresolved until the change is in. Feel free to resolve after you have pushed the commit.

```suggestion
theorem card_iUnion_lt_iff_forall_of_isRegular
    {ι α : Type u} {t : ι → Set α} {c : Cardinal} (hc : c.IsRegular) (hι : #ι < c) :
    #(⋃ i, t i) < c ↔ ∀ i, #(t i) < c := by
```

```suggestion
  refine ⟨card_lt_of_card_iUnion_lt, fun h ↦ ?_⟩
  apply lt_of_le_of_lt (Cardinal.mk_sUnion_le _)
  apply Cardinal.mul_lt_of_lt (Cardinal.IsRegular.aleph0_le hc)
    (lt_of_le_of_lt Cardinal.mk_range_le hι)
  apply Cardinal.iSup_lt_of_isRegular hc (lt_of_le_of_lt Cardinal.mk_range_le hι)
  simpa
```

Is there any reason for this "small difference"? As in, could we have:
```suggestion
which becomes the cardinal `c` union property because we take complements of all sets. -/
def ofCardinalUnion (l : Set (Set α)) (hc : 2 < c)
    (hUnion : ∀ S : Set (Set α), (#S < c) → (∀ s ∈ S, s ∈ l) → ⋃₀ S ∈ l)
    (hmono : ∀ t ∈ l, ∀ s ⊆ t, s ∈ l) : Filter α := by
  refine .ofCardinalInter {s | sᶜ ∈ l} hc (fun S hSc hSp ↦ ?_) fun s t ht hsub ↦ ?_
```
If so please make the corresponding change for `CountableInterFilter`.
(and rename `p` to `l` below)
I initially just adapted the corresponding ones from `CountableInterFilter`, I'll check later today, I'll merge afterwards if I manage
@ocfnash can you check if you like my proof in the last two PR's? If so, I'll merge!
